The paper proposes a novel regularizer for tensor decomposition and completion, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The paper also uses a Bayesian framework to incorporate prior information and enhance the prediction capabilities. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper deals with missing data and uses statistical models, which suggests the sub-categories cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.ST (Statistics) as possible options.
